# TreeSelect

`TxTreeSelect` wraps `TxTree` in a Popover-backed combobox. It supports single-value selection, multiple checked keys, searchable tree filtering, clear actions, custom node rendering, and imperative open/focus helpers.

## Basic Usage

### TreeSelect
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="TreeSelectTreeSelectDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { computed, ref } from 'vue'

  const multiple = ref(false)
  const value = ref<string | number | Array<string | number> | undefined>(undefined)

  const nodes = [
    {
      key: 'general',
      label: 'General',
      children: [
        { key: 'appearance', label: 'Appearance' },
        { key: 'language', label: 'Language' },
      ],
    },
    {
      key: 'account',
      label: 'Account',
      children: [
        { key: 'profile', label: 'Profile' },
        { key: 'billing', label: 'Billing' },
      ],
    },
    {
      key: 'danger',
      label: 'Danger Zone',
      disabled: true,
      children: [
        { key: 'delete', label: 'Delete account', disabled: true },
      ],
    },
  ]

  const placeholder = computed(() => (multiple.value ? 'Select multiple' : 'Select one'))
  </script>

  <template>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; width: 420px;">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center;">
        <TxButton size="small" variant="secondary" @click="multiple = !multiple">
          Toggle multiple
        </TxButton>
        <TxButton size="small" variant="secondary" @click="value = multiple ? [] : undefined">
          Clear
        </TxButton>
      </div>

      <TxTreeSelect
        v-model="value"
        :nodes="nodes"
        :multiple="multiple"
        :placeholder="placeholder"
        :dropdown-max-height="260"
      />

      <div style="color: var(--tx-text-color-secondary); font-size: 12px;">
        value: {{ value }}
      </div>
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

## Admin Ownership Picker

In permission, member, and release-policy pages, `TxTreeSelect` works well for owner teams, namespaces, and organization units. It saves space compared with a full tree and composes naturally with `TxTransfer` and `TxTimeline` in authorization flows.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ComponentsPermissionOrchestrationDemo" code-lang="vue" title="Permission orchestration panel" description="Screenshot-verified owner selection, resource grants, and audit flow."}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const ownerTeam = ref<string | number | undefined>('docs')
  const nodes = [
    {
      key: 'ops',
      label: 'Operations',
      children: [
        { key: 'docs', label: 'Docs maintainers' },
        { key: 'release', label: 'Release managers' },
      ],
    },
  ]
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxTreeSelect
      v-model="ownerTeam"
      :nodes="nodes"
      placeholder="Owner team"
      :default-expanded-keys="['ops']"
      :dropdown-max-height="220"
    />
  </template>
---
:::

## Notes

- `TxTreeSelect` reuses `TxTree` internally. The dropdown tree receives `defaultExpandedKeys`, `filterText`, and `multiple`; it does not expose `expandedKeys` or `filterMethod` controls.
- When `multiple=true`, `modelValue` must be an array and the trigger renders selected labels as tags. Clearing returns `[]`.
- When `multiple=false`, `modelValue` is one key or `undefined`. Selecting a node closes the dropdown, and clearing returns `undefined`.
- Disabled nodes cannot be selected, but their caret can still expand when they have children.

## API

### TxTreeSelect Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `modelValue` | `string \| number \| Array<string \| number> \| undefined` | - | Selected key in single mode, or selected key array in `multiple` mode. |
| `nodes` | `TreeSelectNode[]` | `[]` | Tree nodes displayed in the dropdown and used to resolve trigger labels. |
| `multiple` | `boolean` | `false` | Enables checkbox-style multi-select and tag display in the trigger. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables the trigger, dropdown interaction, keyboard toggling, and clear action. |
| `placeholder` | `string` | `'请选择'` | Placeholder shown when no selected key resolves to a label. |
| `searchable` | `boolean` | `true` | Shows a search input and passes its text to the inner `TxTree` as `filterText`. |
| `clearable` | `boolean` | `true` | Shows a clear button when there is at least one selected key and the component is not disabled. |
| `placement` | `PopoverPlacement` | `'bottom-start'` | Popover placement for the dropdown panel. |
| `dropdownOffset` | `number` | `6` | Popover offset from the trigger. |
| `dropdownWidth` | `number` | `0` | Explicit Popover panel width; `0` leaves width resolution to `TxPopover`. |
| `dropdownMaxWidth` | `number` | `480` | Maximum Popover panel width. |
| `dropdownMaxHeight` | `number` | `320` | Maximum tree panel height in pixels. The list scrolls inside this limit. |
| `defaultExpandedKeys` | `Array<string \| number>` | `[]` | Initial expanded keys passed to the inner `TxTree`. |

### TreeSelectNode

| Field | Type | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `key` | `string \| number` | Stable unique key used as the selected value. |
| `label` | `string` | Visible node label, default search target, and trigger display text. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | Disables selecting this node. |
| `children` | `TreeSelectNode[]` | Optional nested child nodes. |

### TxTreeSelect Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `value: TreeSelectValue` | v-model update emitted after tree selection, clear, or `setValue()`. |
| `change` | `value: TreeSelectValue` | Emitted with the same value immediately after `update:modelValue`. |
| `open` | - | Emitted when the Popover dropdown opens. |
| `close` | - | Emitted when the Popover dropdown closes. |

### TxTreeSelect Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `node` | `{ node, level, expanded, selected }` | Replaces the node label area inside the built-in `TxCardItem` row. Caret, checkbox, padding, and click handling remain owned by the component. |

### Exposed Methods

| Name | Type | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `open()` | `() => void` | Opens the dropdown. |
| `close()` | `() => void` | Closes the dropdown. |
| `toggle()` | `() => void` | Toggles the dropdown open state. |
| `focus()` | `() => void` | Focuses the combobox trigger. |
| `blur()` | `() => void` | Blurs the combobox trigger. |
| `clear()` | `() => void` | Emits `undefined` in single mode or `[]` in multiple mode unless disabled. |
| `setValue(value)` | `(value: TreeSelectValue) => void` | Emits the supplied value through `update:modelValue` and `change`; it does not validate against `nodes`. |
| `getValue()` | `() => TreeSelectValue` | Returns the current `modelValue` prop. |
| `getCheckedKeys()` | `() => Array<string \| number>` | Returns selected keys as an array in both single and multiple modes. |

## Interaction Contract

- The trigger is a focusable `role="combobox"`. `Enter` and `Space` toggle the dropdown; `Escape` closes it.
- The dropdown panel is backed by `TxPopover`; placement and width props pass through to that component.
- Search uses the inner `TxTree` default label filter. There is currently no prop to pass a custom `filterMethod` through `TxTreeSelect`.
- Single selection closes the dropdown after emitting value events. Multiple selection keeps it open for additional checks.
- Trigger labels are resolved from the current `nodes` tree. Unknown selected keys remain selected internally but do not render a visible label.
- `setValue()` is an emitting helper, not internal state. The parent still owns `modelValue` through v-model.
- `setValue` and `getCheckedKeys` are intentionally thin exposed helpers for form wrappers and test harnesses; prefer v-model for normal product code.

## Best Practices

- Use `TxTreeSelect` for compact ownership, namespace, category, and organization-unit selection. Use full `TxTree` when users need persistent context, bulk tree operations, or custom row controls.
- Keep `key` values stable and independent from localized labels; label changes should not invalidate saved selections.
- Match value shape to `multiple` before render. Switching `multiple` at runtime does not coerce an existing scalar into an array or vice versa.
- Prefer shallow default expansion such as root departments or product areas. Deeply expanded dropdowns are harder to scan and scroll.
- Use the `node` slot for badges or secondary labels only; avoid adding separate click targets that compete with the row selection behavior.
- For domain-specific search, wrap the component with an external search experience or use `TxTree` directly until `filterMethod` is exposed.

